Creating a resource group in Azure is a fundamental task for organizing and managing resources.

Steps to create a resource group:

1. Log in to the Azure Portal
2. Navigate to “Resource Groups”
3. Click on “Create”
4. Select the subscription
5. Enter a resource group name
6. Choose a region
7. Review and create

For example, a developer creating a web application can create a resource group named “WebApp-RG” to store all related resources like VMs, databases, and storage.

A real-life use case is project-based management. Each project can have its own resource group, making it easier to manage and delete resources when the project ends.

Another example is testing environments where temporary resource groups can be created and deleted frequently.

This exercise helps users understand practical resource organization in Azure.
